<br>
We've been able to get around the restrictions imposed by TLC for a long time. PoP raids have made it so anyone can do it (unless they have no friends or alts) but even before that it was only a minor problem. I personally outfitted most of the clerics and druids in FnF with Remove Curse using the pet trick (that was over a year ago, BTW, when Remove Curse was actually useful).<br>
<br>
How many problems has buggy NO DROP caused us? Seems like every-other raid someone would have to re-log to clear the NO DROP bug last winter. That's relatively minor, but one has to wonder why it happens, and why it STILL happens...<br>
<br>
And now, the latest idiocy. The magician epic weapon is summoned. Summon one, click it to summon an epic pet, then destroy it because it only has one charge. In order to add an augmentation slot to it they introduced a non-summoned version. All you had to do was run out to Tox Forest and hand a summoned epic weapon to a new NPC and she'd give you a new weapon in return. The new one doesn't have the pet clicky but does have the same stats as the epic weapon, plus it has an augmentation slot. But guess what? It was tradeable! How about that! A tradeable epic. I heard people were selling them (or trying) in the bazaar for 20k. I heard of low-level mages having the non-summoned version now because it was NOT NOT DROP. What makes it worse is: this isn't the first time an epic weapon has been tradeable on FV. Heck, the mage epic itself was tradeable a long time ago. I think the rogue epic was, too.<br>
<br>
Well, the NPC is gone. Those of us (yes me!) that were too late will have to do without until Sony gets around to implementing a NO DROP version of the non-summoned mage epic weapon. Of course, they also have to figure out what to do about all the epics that got traded. And what about the ones that were traded and later augmented? People aren't going to be happy if the weapon just goes *poof*!<br>
<br>
We've already got the screwiest server economy going. I suppose it is THAT which will keep TLC from ever being changed. Too many people have dedicated too many resources to the TLC economy for Sony to change it now.<br>
<br>
And you know what? The population is booming! All those nay-sayers that predicted FV would be shut down because no one wanted to play here were wrong, although they may be been right when they said it, hehe. Sony keeps tweaking the ruleset for us, the population keeps growing, and the TLC bugs just won't go away. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=237657"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.redhills.com/img/enannsig.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=witherweaver>Witherweaver</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 708<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/15/03 11:48 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4043.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What good is TLC?</span><hr size=1> Warrior epic was not no drop originally, too.  That was neat because you could make infinitely many of them.<br>
