<br>
But, at the same time, No Drop was removed, so, when you out grew equipment you could hand it down to someone, or sell it. Like you would in real life. <br>
<br>
And it all worked well till pop raid feature came out, to get around TLC. Suddenly, you had farmers every where. I had problems with a shaman in LGuk training everyone there so he could farm all the items uncontested. I wasn't the only one either who ran into this person (No need for names, the issue has long since be resolved)<br>
<br>
You see farming all the time. Because TLC can be bypassed and all items from it sold in the bazaar, more people are intersted in doing that.<br>
<br>
On top, you have lots of players that do nothing more then spend their time in the bazaar buying low and selling high. That doesn't bother me too much. Now that some players have obviously accuminalted millions, they are buying any high end gear they can, regardless of the price, and then marking it up more, because they know the rarity of it. Not to mention that you can now have up to 20 duplicate lore items, because of the shared bank slots. <br>
<br>
That's fine, for me, since paying 100,000 for one item isn't anything I plan on doing. It won't make me enjoy the game anymore then I already do. <br>
<br>
But it has ruined our economy, and the idea behind a rollplaying server, there are more rollPAYers then players. Meaning, they are more bazaared then twinked in the old fashioned sense of the word twink. The only people that don't think the economy is ruined are those that have tons of money. But then, that's kinda like real life, isn't it? Those few with the money don't see a problem with poverity. <br>
<br>
And that's why FV has seen an influx of people that are greedy. Because they know that 98% of everything is for sale on this server. I suspect there is more buying of gear and plat on this server then other servers for that simple reason. <br>
<br>
I've encountered more and more people that have no clue where thier gear comes from, they bought it all. And some of it is truely nice gear. Gear they couldn't have gotten themselves, and gear I know that costs lots of money, yet these people don't have a clue on how to make any money in game. To me, that makes me think they bought thier plat, and continue to do so. Short on money, 10-30 dollars can fix that quick. <br>
<br>
In the end, it does't bother me to much. I'm not interested in telling others how to play. And, if I encounter someone I think was eBayed, and they suck in thier class, me and my friends snicker behind thier back and never group with them again and we let our friends (not strangers we don't know), know that they stink, and should avoid them.<br>
<br>
But back to TLC. With an easy way to get around it, it's stupid to have. But just removing it would cause more issues. <br>
<br>
I always felt the idea behind the bazaar was so that tradeskillers could sell the things they made. That's why it's full of ovens and looms and forges and anything you need to make items. <br>
<br>
To take this server back towards rollplaying more, I would like to see a new tag, called No Sale. Meaning, you can't sell it in trader mode. Basically, take the No Drop, and make it so when placed in a traders satchel, it won't show up when people are browsing your wares. You can't put a price on it.<br>
<br>
Sure, this makes you say, well, whats to stop them from just spamming the bazaar with shouts for these items. Whats to stop them from making a macro spamming shouts. <br>
<br>
Nothing is stopping them. But I suspect, that at first, it will be really bad. It's already pretty bad in the Bazaar and PoK. In time, people will get sick of the spam, and either put those players on ignore, or turn shouts off. And in time, it will settle into something tolerable.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=caillougna>Caillou GNA</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.tshrew.net/caillou/sigs/dot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Pebble with a bow</span><br>  Posts: 1903<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/15/03 1:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4043.topic&index=7>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.tshrew.net/caillou/sigs/smile.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What good is TLC?</span><hr size=1> The examples you cited were problems with the NO DROP flags and not TLC.  Yes, one is always cited as the reason/compensation for the other, but they are totally different than each other.<br>
<br>
Yes, there have been many NO DROP bugs on this server at various times.  There are still, I thik, some GM tradeskill items which produce a droppable bag or are themselves droppable.  There are times (for me usually after a partial crash) when a client comes up like it is on a blue server.  And so on.<br>
<br>
TLC is not NO DROP, TLC is only that which makes the magic and lore items not drop if you are too high of a level to be fighting that target.  TLC is intended to make targets available for those who are level-appropriate.  Lack of NO DROP allows those who are level-appropriate to gather things (farm) to sell to those who are not (either too high or too low).   <p><center><table width="55%"><tr><td align="center">
